pdqninja.util
Class WeightedLoopIterator<E>

java.lang.Object
  pdqninja.util.WeightedLoopIterator<E>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<E>
Direct Known Subclasses:
FileStoreIterator
public class WeightedLoopIterator<E>
extends Object
implements Iterator<E>

Iterate in a loop over an array of objects, in ratios determined by their specified weight.

As an example, for a collection of items [Item1, Item2, Item3] with weights [2, 1, 3], the WeightedLoopIterator will iterate as follows:

Item1, Item1, Item2, Item3, Item3, Item3, Item1, Item1, Item2, ...

Notice the first six entries - the items are returned in ratio of their relative weights. Also notice that the pattern repeats itself indefinitely, that is, hasNext() will always return true.

This iterator allows items to be removed, in which case the weight of the removed item will be set to zero. Only when all items are removed (or equivalently, when the sum of weights is zero), hasNext() will return false.

cycle() methods returns the periodicity of the loop, which is equal to the sum of the weights of the items.
